# 🤝🌈 Code of Conduct Extraordinaire! 🚀✨

## 🤲 Our Awesome Pledge 🌍

As the maintainer and contributors of this project, I 🤝 pledge to make participation in this project and community a super-inclusive, harassment-free experience for EVERYONE 🌈, regardless of:
- 👶 Age
- 🏋️ Body size
- ♿ Disability
- 🌍 Ethnicity
- 🏳️‍🌈 Gender identity and expression
- 🎓 Level of experience
- 🌐 Nationality
- 👀 Personal appearance
- 🌈 Race
- 🙏 Religion
- ❤️ Sexual identity and orientation

## 🌟 Our Stellar Standards

Examples of behavior that creates a MAGICAL positive environment include:

* 💬 Using welcoming and inclusive language 🤗
* 🔄 Being respectful of differing viewpoints and experiences 🧠
* 🎓 Gracefully accepting constructive criticism 🏆
* 🎯 Focusing on what is best for the community 🌈
* 💖 Showing empathy towards other community members 🤗

Examples of TOTALLY UNACCEPTABLE behavior include:

* 🚫 The use of sexualized language or imagery and unwelcome sexual attention or advances 😱
* 🤬 Trolling, insulting/derogatory comments, and personal or political attacks 💥
* 😈 Public or private harassment 🚫
* 🕵️ Publishing others' private information without explicit permission 🚨
* 🙅‍♀️ Other conduct which could reasonably be considered inappropriate in a professional setting 🚫

## 🛡️ Enforcement Responsibilities

As the project maintainer, I am responsible for:
- 🔍 Clarifying standards of acceptable behavior
- ⚖️ Taking appropriate and fair corrective action
- 🛡️ Responding to inappropriate, threatening, offensive, or harmful behavior

## 🌐 Scope of Awesomeness

This Code of Conduct applies:
- 🏠 Within project spaces
- 🌍 In public spaces when representing the project
- 📧 Using official project communication channels
- 🤝 At online and offline events


## 🙏 Attribution

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the legendary [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org), version 2.0 🌟🤝

# 🤝 Code of Conduct

## 📝 Introduction

As a solo student developer maintaining this open-source project, I want to create a welcoming environment for everyone who wishes to use, contribute to, or engage with this portfolio template.

## 🌟 Our Standards

I value:

* 💬 Friendly and constructive communication
* 🧠 Diverse perspectives and ideas
* 🤝 Mutual respect between all participants
* 💡 Helpful feedback and suggestions
* 🌱 Supporting newcomers to coding and open source

## ❌ Unacceptable Behavior

The following behaviors are not welcome:

* 🚫 Harassment or discrimination of any kind
* 🤬 Aggressive or disrespectful comments
* 🕵️ Sharing private information without permission
* 🔥 Trolling or purposely disruptive behavior
* 🤖 Spam or irrelevant self-promotion

## 🛡️ My Commitment

As the maintainer of this project, I commit to:

* 👂 Being responsive to questions and feedback
* 🧐 Reviewing contributions fairly
* 🛠️ Maintaining the project to the best of my ability as a student
* 🤔 Being open to suggestions for improvement
* 🙌 Acknowledging the work of contributors

## 💬 Communication

All project discussions will happen in GitHub issues and pull requests. Keep communication public so others can learn and benefit from the exchange of ideas.

## 👋 Final Note

This is a learning project created by a student developer. While I'm committed to this Code of Conduct, please understand that my response times may vary due to academic commitments.

Thank you for understanding and for being part of this journey! 🎓
